in the dir ~/Work/SoftwareMindset/ set up VScode project
via pyenv manage working envs

Pyenv setup for system.
 1709  pyenv --version
 1711  pyenv global  # display main python on system
 1712  python --version  # it is the same here
 1714  pyenv install --list  # list available python versions
# if pyenv version is too old, pull the newest, to gain access to newer pythons
 1715  cd ~/.pyenv/
 1716  git pull
 1717  pyenv --version  # newer pyenv
 1718  pyenv install --list  # more pythons
 1719  cd ~/Work/SoftwareMindset/
 1720  pyenv install 3.10.5
 1721  pyenv versions  # show what is available in system
# create venv for the project software mindset
 1727  pyenv virtualenv 3.10.5 venv310
 1728  pyenv local venv310
 1729  which python
 1730  python --version
# to Select Interpreter in VSCode reload window, home+F1-> Select Int..-> ~/.pyenv/versions/3.10.5/envs/venv310/bin/python

